{"word":"H3293 - יַעַר - yaʻar - yah'-ar - Comb","slug":"H3293","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יַעַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yaʻar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yah'-ar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Comb"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E2;&#x05E8; - ya&#x201B;ar</b> - <i>yah'-ar</i><p/>From an unused root probably meaning to <i>thicken</i> with verdure; a <i>copse</i> of bushes; hence a <i>forest</i>; hence <i>honey</i> in the <i>comb</i> (as hived in trees): - [honey-] comb, forest, wood."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3294\">H3294</a>, <a href=\"#/H3295\">H3295</a>, <a href=\"#/H3296\">H3296</a>, <a href=\"#/H3297\">H3297</a>, <a href=\"#/H3301\">H3301</a>"}]}